Gaupol 0.16
===========

 [D] Use existing subtitle file mime-types instead of text/plain when
     adding files to the recent files database
 [D] Fix opening a translation file with a Unicode BOM
 [D] Add German translation (Chris Leick)
 [D] Add Hungarian translation (László Andrássy)

 [ ] Split gaupol to aeidon and gaupol
 [ ] Bump Python dependency to 2.6
      - Remove imports from __future__
      - http://docs.python.org/dev/whatsnew/2.6.html
 [ ] Bump PyGObject dependency to 2.16
      - Try gobject.option.OptionParser (see #378704)
      - Try gio.AppInfo for launching web browser and video player
 [ ] Bump PyGTK dependency to 2.14
      - Try gtk.show_uri for launching web browser
 [ ] Bump PyEnchant dependency to 1.4
      - All dictionary providers now use a shared default personal word
        file (largely obsoleting the DictWithPWL class)
      - Dict.add_to_pwl renamed to Dict.add
 [ ] Add gaupol.gtk.View.add_column, which creates a new model
 [ ] Migrate from Glade to gtk.Builder
 [ ] Adapt to GNOME Goal: Correct Desktop Files
 [ ] Adapt to new GTK+/GNOME anti-icon policy for buttons
 [ ] Code cleanup, attribute and signals checks
 [ ] Merge experimental local patterns
 [ ] Use decorator module to preserve signatures in API documentation
      - http://pypi.python.org/pypi/decorator/
 [ ] Fix focus changing when pasting subtitles
      - http://www.mail-archive.com/gaupol-list@gna.org/msg00022.html
 [ ] Use gtk.accel_map_load and gtk.accel_map_save
 [?] Use transifex.net (or something) for translations
 [ ] Use gtk.RecentAction for the recent file menus
 [ ] Save text correction assistant window size
 [ ] http://tecnocode.co.uk/2009/10/01/unicode-in-gnome/
 [ ] Mark strings containing Unicode ellipses as unicode strings (u"")
     or add unicode function calls for i18n functions
 [ ] MetadataItem._get_localized_field should try 'xx' if 'xx_YY'
     fails
 [?] Add help menu item for wiki page
 [?] http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=555338
 [?] Copy key-event hack from gedit for sidepane
      - http://mail.gnome.org/archives/desktop-devel-list/2009-November/msg00263.html
 [?] http://gmane.org/
 [?] http://docs.python.org/library/json.html

